    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 30th with a high-ceiling core, led by **Yordan Alvarez** (87.42) and **Kyle Schwarber** (75.99). **Yordan Alvarez** is our clear top play, benefiting from a massive 16% park boost and favorable matchup against Young; his xwOBA of .393 suggests he is primed to drive the offense. Similarly, **Kyle Schwarber** provides immense value in the number two slot, where an elite BvP history against Houser (+8%) and a top-tier xwOBA (.402) offset the minor platoon drag. **Trea Turner** (72.20) rounds out our elite tier; while Houser is a respectable arm, **Trea Turner**\u2019s leadoff positioning and scarcity in the SB category make him an indispensable anchor for our 5x5 objectives today.\n\nOur middle-tier starters **Colt Keith** (63.34) and **Kazuma Okamoto** (60.36) offer stable production, with **Colt Keith** gaining significant value from his promotion to the #3 spot. Meanwhile, **Carson Benge** (56.03) sits at the edge of our efficiency window; he is a marginal start against Mikolas, and while the 19% SP skill adjustment helps his case, he will remain on a short leash. The most difficult bench decision involved **Jerar Encarnacion** (39.39), who fell just shy of our 40.0 floor. Despite a decent platoon advantage, the combination of S\u00e1nchez\u2019s stingy pitching profile and a bottom-of-the-order assignment made him a liability compared to our active starters.\n\nWe are monitoring the status of **Christian Yelich**, **Hyeseong Kim**, **Zac Veen**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Chase Meidroth**, **Gary Sanchez**, **Luke Raley**, **Josh Smith**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pedro Ramirez**, and **Luis Pena** for any late-breaking roster news, though they are currently idle or benched. We are also tracking **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Junior Caminero**, and **Caleb Durbin**, all of whom are unavailable today due to team off-days. Outside of the weather risks associated with the Houser and Young matchups, we expect our active roster to prioritize SB efficiency and HR upside to maintain our current standing.",
